Just a woman and her pumpkins 🎃🤣 I tried the viral terracotta pumpkin hack and it was SO easy and affordable. I’ll link the pumpkins I used, but you could use whatever you want! For paint, I used the color “poncho” from Behr. After I applied the second coat of paint, I waited until it was about half way dry and then sprinkled on baking soda and rubbed it in gently.
